{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846737239,"sessionID":"ses_28749f2f4ffeLUsnYfYJHFuunK","part":{"id":"prt_d78b6c33d001S2P60fac9ZWV69","messageID":"msg_d78b6b65f001A0pCVRRefsIN4x","sessionID":"ses_28749f2f4ffeLUsnYfYJHFuunK","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the proposal for AR-008. Let me create the proposal.md file:","time":{"start":1775846737237,"end":1775846737237}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846798186,"sessionID":"ses_28749f2f4ffeLUsnYfYJHFuunK","part":{"id":"prt_d78b6c557001FiyMGl72f1AOyD","messageID":"msg_d78b6b65f001A0pCVRRefsIN4x","sessionID":"ses_28749f2f4ffeLUsnYfYJHFuunK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_809833a557eb4b29a381343b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/proposal.md","content":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a time-based garbage collection mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager` to automatically clean up idle and expired sandboxes. The GarbageCollector periodically scans the store for sandboxes that exceed idle timeout or max session duration thresholds, then deletes them via Kubernetes API and removes their metadata from the store. This ensures resource efficiency and prevents sandbox leakage in production environments.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **Component** | `GarbageCollector` struct with lifecycle management |\n| **GVRs managed** | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim` |\n| **Cleanup triggers** | Idle timeout (no activity for 15m), Max session duration exceeded (8h) |\n| **Store operations** | `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n| **Audit logging** | klog-based cleanup audit entries with success/failure status |\n| **Default timing** | GC interval: 15s, Batch size: 16, Single tick timeout: 2m |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Idle timeout configuration per `AgentRuntime` CR (uses global `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`)\n- `agentd` reconciler for sandbox-side idle tracking (separate AR)\n- Custom cleanup policies or hooks\n- Resource quota enforcement\n- Metrics/monitoring integration\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | `GarbageCollector` struct, constructor, lifecycle methods, cleanup logic |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC initialization, loop behavior, cleanup scenarios |\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n    GCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n    DeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n)\n```\n\n### GVR definitions\n\n```go\nvar (\n    SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n        Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n        Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n        Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n    }\n\n    SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n        Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n        Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n        Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n    }\n)\n```\n\n### GarbageCollector struct\n\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    dynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n    storeClient   store.Store\n    interval      time.Duration\n    ctx           context.Context\n    cancel        context.CancelFunc\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewGarbageCollector(\n    dynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n    storeClient store.Store,\n    interval time.Duration,\n) *GarbageCollector {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    return &GarbageCollector{\n        dynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n        storeClient:   storeClient,\n        interval:      interval,\n        ctx:           ctx,\n        cancel:        cancel,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Lifecycle methods\n\n**Start**: launches `gcLoop` in background goroutine\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n    go gc.gcLoop()\n}\n```\n\n**Stop**: cancels context to terminate loop\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n    gc.cancel()\n}\n```\n\n### gcLoop algorithm\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) gcLoop() {\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n\n    klog.Info(\"GarbageCollector started\")\n\n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-gc.ctx.Done():\n            klog.Info(\"GarbageCollector stopped\")\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            gc.tick()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### tick cleanup logic\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) tick() {\n    tickCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(gc.ctx, GCSingleTickTimeout)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    now := time.Now()\n    idleThreshold := now.Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)\n    expiredThreshold := now\n\n    // Clean up idle sandboxes\n    idleSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListInactiveSandboxes(tickCtx, idleThreshold, 16)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Errorf(\"Failed to list inactive sandboxes: %v\", err)\n    } else {\n        for _, sandbox := range idleSandboxes {\n            gc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonIdleTimeout)\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Clean up expired sandboxes\n    expiredSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListExpiredSandboxes(tickCtx, expiredThreshold, 16)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Errorf(\"Failed to list expired sandboxes: %v\", err)\n    } else {\n        for _, sandbox := range expiredSandboxes {\n            gc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonExpired)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### deleteSandbox algorithm\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) deleteSandbox(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sandbox *types.SandboxInfo,\n    reason wmTypes.SandboxCleanupReason,\n) {\n    auditEntry := &wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry{\n        SessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n        SandboxID: sandbox.SandboxID,\n        Namespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace,\n        Reason:    reason,\n        DeletedAt: time.Now(),\n    }\n\n    gvr := SandboxGVR\n    if sandbox.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" {\n        gvr = SandboxClaimGVR\n    }\n\n    deleteCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, DeleteTimeout)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    err := gc.dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).\n        Namespace(sandbox.SandboxNamespace).\n        Delete(deleteCtx, sandbox.SandboxID, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n\n    if err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        auditEntry.ErrorMessage = err.Error()\n        auditEntry.Success = false\n        klog.Errorf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s/%s: %v\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, err)\n    } else {\n        if err := gc.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sandbox.SessionID); err != nil {\n            klog.Warningf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s from store: %v\", sandbox.SessionID, err)\n        }\n        auditEntry.Success = true\n        klog.Infof(\"Deleted sandbox %s/%s (reason: %s)\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, reason)\n    }\n\n    gc.recordAudit(auditEntry)\n}\n```\n\n### Audit logging\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) recordAudit(entry *wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry) {\n    klog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit: sessionId=%s sandboxId=%s namespace=%s reason=%s success=%v deletedAt=%s\",\n        entry.SessionID, entry.SandboxID, entry.Namespace, entry.Reason, entry.Success, entry.DeletedAt.Format(time.RFC3339))\n    if entry.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n        klog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit error: %s\", entry.ErrorMessage)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### CleanupAuditEntry type (`pkg/workloadmanager/types`)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxCleanupReason string\n\nconst (\n    CleanupReasonIdleTimeout SandboxCleanupReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n    CleanupReasonExpired     SandboxCleanupReason = \"Expired\"\n)\n\ntype CleanupAuditEntry struct {\n    SessionID   string\n    SandboxID   string\n    Namespace   string\n    Reason      SandboxCleanupReason\n    DeletedAt   time.Time\n    Success     bool\n    ErrorMessage string\n}\n```\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | ~150 |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types/cleanup.go` | ~30 |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go` | Add GC initialization and start in startup sequence |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Export `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, `DefaultSandboxTTL` constants |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Handle `IsNotFound` gracefully |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured audit logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | List and delete sandbox metadata |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Calls `NewGarbageCollector` and `Start()` |\n| `pkg/store` | Must implement `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `ListExpiredSandboxes` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Imports `CleanupAuditEntry`, `SandboxCleanupReason` |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new background service. No existing APIs or behaviors are modified. The GC operates transparently on existing sandbox resources.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **GC interval**: 15s (configurable via constructor)\n- **Batch size**: 16 sandboxes per tick (prevents API throttling)\n- **Single tick timeout**: 2m (prevents runaway goroutines)\n- **Delete timeout**: 30s per sandbox (prevents hanging on slow deletes)\n- **Store queries**: 2x per tick (idle list + expired list)\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Store unavailable**: Error logged, tick completes silently, retries next interval\n2. **Sandbox already deleted**: `IsNotFound` treated as success\n3. **Delete fails**: Error logged, sandbox remains in store, will be retried next tick\n4. **Context cancelled during delete**: Timeout context ensures cleanup completes or aborts cleanly\n5. **Kind mismatch**: GVR selected dynamically based on `sandbox.Kind` field\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Use controller-runtime manager with Reconciler pattern\n\n**Approach**: Implement GC as a controller-runtime reconciler that watches Sandbox resources and triggers cleanup based on annotation timestamps.\n\n**Rejected because**: \n- Workload Manager is a Gin-based HTTP service, not a controller-runtime application\n- Adding controller-runtime would introduce significant complexity and runtime overhead\n- Time-based cleanup is more efficiently handled by polling than by reconciler requeue patterns\n- Current architecture already has a dedicated `agentd` reconciler for sandbox-side idle tracking\n\n### 2. Event-driven cleanup via Kubernetes TTL controller\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes built-in TTL (`metadata.deletionTimestamp` + `ttlSecondsAfterFinish`) to auto-delete expired sandboxes.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- TTL only handles max duration, not idle timeout (requires last-activity tracking)\n- Would require changes to sandbox controller to set deletion timestamps\n- Less flexible for custom cleanup logic (audit logging, store cleanup)\n- Doesn't integrate with application-level session metadata in Redis store\n\n### 3. Per-session goroutine with `time.AfterFunc`\n\n**Approach**: When creating a sandbox, spawn a goroutine with `time.AfterFunc(idleTimeout, cleanupCallback)` that fires when idle.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Memory leak risk: thousands of sessions = thousands of goroutines\n- Difficult to track/update idle timeout when activity occurs\n- No centralized visibility into cleanup state\n- Harder to test and debug than centralized polling loop\n\n### 4. External cron job / Kubernetes CronJob\n\n**Approach**: Run cleanup as an external scheduled job that calls workload-manager API or directly deletes resources.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Adds operational complexity (separate deployment, RBAC, monitoring)\n- Tighter integration with store requires direct DB access or extra API endpoints\n- Less responsive than in-process GC (cron interval typically minutes, not seconds)\n- Audit logging and error handling more complex across process boundaries\n\n### 5. Configurable GC interval and batch size\n\n**Approach**: Expose `interval` and `batchSize` as CLI flags or config options.\n\n**Deferred because**: Current hardcoded defaults (15s interval, 16 batch) are sufficient for initial deployment. Can be made configurable if production monitoring shows need for tuning.\n\n## Integration with Server\n\n### Server struct addition\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    garbageCollector *GarbageCollector\n}\n```\n\n### Startup sequence in `Run()` method\n\n```go\n// After storeClient and k8sClient initialization\ngc := NewGarbageCollector(k8sClient.dynamicClient, storeClient, 15*time.Second)\ns.garbageCollector = gc\ngc.Start()\n```\n\n### Shutdown sequence\n\n```go\n// In graceful shutdown\nif s.garbageCollector != nil {\n    s.garbageCollector.Stop()\n}\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Run unit tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollector\n\n# Verify no generated files need updating\nmake gen-check\n\n# Integration test (manual)\n# 1. Create sandbox via API\n# 2. Wait for idle timeout (15m)\n# 3. Verify sandbox deleted and audit log entry present\n```\n\n## Testing strategy\n\n### Unit tests (`garbage_collector_test.go`)\n\n1. **TestNewGarbageCollector**: Verify constructor initializes all fields correctly\n2. **TestGarbageCollector_StartStop**: Verify goroutine lifecycle (start, stop, no panic)\n3. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_IdleCleanup**: Mock store returns idle sandbox, verify delete called\n4. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_ExpiredCleanup**: Mock store returns expired sandbox, verify delete called\n5. **TestGarbageCollector_deleteSandbox_NotFound**: Verify `IsNotFound` treated as success\n6. **TestGarbageCollector_deleteSandbox_StoreError**: Verify error logged but audit recorded\n7. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_ContextTimeout**: Verify tick respects context timeout\n8. **TestGarbageCollector_tick_StoreError**: Verify error logged, loop continues\n\n### Test helpers\n\n```go\nfunc newFakeStore() *fakeStore {\n